description: The DDCA has, however, not included Rishabh Pant, Virat Kohli, and Harshit Rana in the official 16-member squad, as they will only be available for limited matches — likely two to three — before India’s ODI series against New Zealand, starting January 11, 2026. The exact fixtures in which Kohli and Pant will play are yet to be confirmed.
title: Virat Kohli returns; Rishabh Pant to lead Delhi in Vijay Hazare Trophy — Full squad

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: South Africa coach Shukri Conrad deemed the India tour successful despite a T20I series loss, expressing hope for a rematch in the next T20 World Cup final. Conrad, who faced criticism during the second and final Test in Guwahati for using the word ‘grovel’, also reflected on the learning experience of touring India.
title: Will India and South Africa meet in 2026 T20 World Cup final? Shukri Conrad hopes so

author: BHAVIKA JAIN
description: Navi Mumbai International Airport (NMIA), opening December 25, will initially have higher user development fees than Mumbai airport. Adani Group aims for a unified tariff, making prices comparable soon. NMIA will also help alleviate Mumbai's severe capacity constraints by shifting some peak-hour flights.
title: Couple of peak-hour flights to be moved to Navi Mumbai to ease congestion

author: SAURABH SINHA
description: Winters in Delhi once meant a sensory delight of seasonal foods, from makke ki roti to halwa. However, recent years have brought deadly pollution, replacing aromatic food whiffs with the smell of burning and health concerns. Despite this, foodies still brave the smog to savor traditional street food, though conversations now revolve around pollution and sore throats.
title: Chat cart: When your tandoori naan & tikka aren’t smoky, but everything else is

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: An Air India Express pilot has been grounded after allegedly assaulting a passenger at Delhi Airport's Terminal 1. The altercation began when the pilot questioned a passenger using a staff lane, escalating into a physical confrontation. The passenger claims he was left with a bloodied face and his daughter traumatized. An inquiry is underway.
title: 'Are you anpadh': Verbal argument at Delhi airport escalates into physical assault by AIX pilot

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated Guwahati's new Lokapriya Gopinath Bardoloi International Airport terminal today, a significant infrastructure upgrade for Assam. This nature-themed facility, featuring a 'Sky Forest' with indigenous plants, aims to enhance passenger experience and boost commerce and tourism. The terminal is designed to handle millions of passengers annually, incorporating modern digital features for efficient travel.
title: Guwahati airport gets new terminal! PM Modi to inaugurate today - see stunning pics

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India's squad for the 2026 T20 World Cup and the New Zealand series is set to be announced on Saturday. The leadership duo of captain Suryakumar Yadav and vice-captain Shubman Gill is expected to retain their spots despite a challenging year. Suryakumar has managed 213 runs in 18 innings at an average of 14.20 with no fifties, while Gill has scored 291 runs in 15 innings at an average of 24.25 and remains without a fifty since his T20I return.
title: India T20 World Cup 2026 squad announcement: Time, date, venue and live streaming details

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Mumbai is set to get a world-class marina in its harbour, a Rs 887-crore project approved by the Union government. This initiative aims to boost maritime tourism and waterfront development, creating over 2,000 jobs. The facility will accommodate 424 yachts and includes plans for a sailing school and extensive onshore amenities, positioning Mumbai as a global maritime hub.
title: Mumbai Marina project: Centre clears Rs 887cr world-class plan — top things to know

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Veteran Malayalam actor and director Sreenivasan passed away at a private hospital near Kochi on Saturday morning at the age of 69. A native of Kannur, he had been living in Kochi for years and appeared in over 200 films. Sreenivasan was also a director, screenwriter, dubbing artist, and producer.
title: Noted Malayalam actor-director Sreenivasan passes away at 69 in Kochi; starred in over 200 films

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Violence erupted in Dhaka following the fatal shooting of youth leader Sharif Osman Hadi. Hundreds of his supporters allegedly set fire to the offices of Prothom Alo and The Daily Star newspapers. The executive editor described it as a "darkest night" for the media, with journalists forced to flee.
title: ‘Scared to death': B'desh newspaper goes unpublished for first time; editor recounts 'darkest night'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The United States has imposed sanctions on seven individuals linked to Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro and his wife, Cilia Flores. The Treasury Department accused them of supporting Maduro's "rogue narcostate" and threatening regional stability. This action follows a series of US military buildups and operations in the Caribbean aimed at pressuring Maduro's government.
title: Trump Vs Nicolas: US imposes sanctions on family members: Who are they?

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US launched a major military operation in Syria. Over seventy Islamic State targets were hit with more than one hundred precision munitions. This action follows the recent killing of two American personnel in a December 13 attack. ​Trump said the strikes were part of "Operation Hawkeye Strike" and warned any group threatening Americans of severe consequences.
title: Watch: US strikes over 70 targets in Syria; calls it 'declaration of vengeance'

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Starbucks has appointed Anand Varadarajan, an Indian-origin tech leader with extensive experience from Amazon, as its new Chief Technology Officer, effective January 19. This strategic move aligns with CEO Brian Niccol's vision for a significant technology overhaul aimed at enhancing in-store operational efficiency. Varadarajan's expertise will be crucial in driving this transformation.
title: Who is Anand Varadarajan? Starbucks appoints Indian national as chief technology officer

author: LACHIT ROY
description: Sibley Scoles emerged as a standout during Netflix’s broadcast of Jake Paul vs Anthony Joshua, impressing viewers with her confident ringside reporting. An Emmy-winning broadcaster, Scoles is known for her work with the Las Vegas Raiders, E! News, and major live events. Her appearance introduced a global audience to a seasoned media professional comfortable on the biggest stages.
title: Who is Sibley Scoles? Netflix ringside reporter at Jake Paul vs Joshua

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Boost your winter immunity with nutrient-rich foods that support your immune system and combat respiratory infections. Experts highlight micronutrients and live microbes found in citrus, leafy greens, fermented dairy, and zinc-rich seeds, which can reduce infection risk and duration. Incorporating these foods into your diet provides essential vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants for your body's defense.
title: Winter​‍​‌‍​‍‌​‍​‌‍​‍‌ immunity-boosting foods: What to eat to stay well when temperature drops

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Eight elephants tragically died after being struck by the Sairang New Delhi Rajdhani Express in Assam's Hojai district early Saturday. The collision caused five coaches and the engine of the train to derail, though no passengers were injured. The incident occurred in a forested area known for elephant movement.
title: Assam tragedy: Rajdhani Express hits herd of elephants, killing 8; engine, 5 coaches derail

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: Delhi-NCR wakes up to toxic smog: AQI hits ‘very poor’ to ‘severe’ levels; flights impacted

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Hardik Pandya's explosive 63 off 25 balls powered India to a 30-run victory and a 3-1 series win against South Africa. His rapid half-century and a crucial partnership with Tilak Varma set a massive target. Pandya's sportsmanship, checking on a cameraman hit by his six, also drew praise. Varun Chakravarthy's four wickets sealed the win.
title: Hardik Pandya's monster hit injures cameraman; ice pack, hug follow - WATCH

author: SAHIL MALHOTRA
description: With a 50-day countdown to the 2026 T20 World Cup, India’s think-tank has made workload management its top priority, ring-fencing Jasprit Bumrah and Hardik Pandya. Bumrah will skip the New Zealand ODIs, while Pandya’s domestic appearances will be carefully rationed, as the management prioritises peak fitness and continuity in T20Is over all other formats.
title: T20 World Cup | India think tank’s top priority: Keeping Bumrah and Pandya fresh

author: SINDHU KANNAN
description: A chilling murder plot unfolded in Tiruvallur district where two sons allegedly orchestrated their father's death by snakebite to claim ₹3 crore in insurance.  Initially ruled accidental, the investigation revealed a staged second bite by a krait after a previous cobra incident. Six individuals, including the sons, have been arrested.
title: Tamil Nadu: Lab assistant dies after 'snakebite'; sons plotted murder for Rs 3 cr insurance

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A Reddit tip about a suspicious car with Florida plates near Brown University led police to Claudio Manuel Neves Valente, the suspect in a deadly campus shooting and the murder of an MIT professor. Valente, a former Brown graduate student, died by suicide in a storage unit. Investigators are still probing his motives.
title: Brown University shooting: How a Reddit post helped police track the shooter

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US President Trump announced agreements with nine major pharmaceutical companies to lower prescription drug prices in the US, aligning them with those in other wealthy nations. These deals will impact Medicaid pricing and introduce "most-favoured-nation" pricing for new drugs across all markets. Companies also committed to a direct-to-consumer platform and offered discounts.
title: Cheaper medicines push: Trump strikes deals with 9 major pharma firms

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: An auto driver kidnapped two minor sisters, sexually assaulting the elder one in Manesar. A passerby alerted police, leading to a chase. The accused jumped from a flyover, sustaining leg fractures, and was apprehended. He faces charges under the POCSO Act.
title: Gurgaon horror: Auto driver rapes minor, kidnaps 2 girls; jumps off flyover to evade arrest

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A former gym trainer, Ranjan M, has been accused by parents in Thyagarajanagar of targeting several children with bike incidents and physical assaults. The most serious case involved a five-year-old boy who was kicked while playing. Police confirm Ranjan appears mentally unstable and is undergoing treatment, having confessed to the assaults due to agitation from children playing.
title: 'I feel distracted when kids play': Ex-gym trainer assaults multiple children in Bengaluru

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi is grappling with severe smog, leading to travel advisories and weather alerts. The India Meteorological Department has issued yellow and orange alerts for dense fog, impacting flight operations. Air quality has plummeted to hazardous levels across the city, prompting authorities to implement stringent pollution control measures.
title: Orange alert in Delhi-NCR: AQI soars to 633; visibility and flights impacted

author: TNN
description: Authorities investigating the Lionel Messi event's mismanagement raided chief organizer Satadru Dutta's home, uncovering a lavish residence with a pool and soccer ground. The probe has broadened beyond crowd control to suspected Rs 100 crore financial irregularities, including unaccounted cash for photos with Messi and opaque ticket sales, suggesting deliberate financial impropriety.
title: 'Rs 30 lakh to take image with Messi’: Kolkata police raid organiser Satadru Dutta’s house

author: TNN
description: The Supreme Court has signaled its strong inclination to protect elephants, stating it will always favor animals whose migration paths are obstructed by commercial tourism. This stance emerged during hearings concerning wildlife resorts in Tamil Nadu's Sigur Plateau elephant corridor. The court emphasized that any doubt regarding benefit should go to the silent victims of development.
title: Court will always lean towards animals who suffer silently: Supreme Court

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Ranveer Singh's 'Dhurandhar' has achieved remarkable success, dominating the box office for 15 days. The film has already crossed Rs 730 crore globally, with an impressive Rs 483 crore net collection in India. Even with new releases, 'Dhurandhar' continues to hold its number one position.
title: ‘Dhurandhar’ box office day 15: Ranveer Singh–Akshaye Khanna starrer continues to reign; mints Rs 730 cr globally

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Winter in North India brings delicious delicacies like gajar ka halwa, butter chicken, and pakode. However, these treats, while delightful, pose significant risks to heart health due to high fat, sugar, and calorie content. Dr. Manan Aggarwal warns that these indulgences can exacerbate the natural thickening of blood and increased workload on the heart during colder months.
title: Gajar Halwa, Gajak on autopilot? Put heart health first this winter, warns physician

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: AWS CEO Matt Garman acknowledges initial concerns about Amazon's AI narrative but asserts the company's strong position. He highlights AWS's robust agentic platform, broad model selection, and comprehensive security controls, emphasizing their focus on enterprise solutions rather than consumer applications like ChatGPT. Garman is pleased with the current perception of AWS in the AI landscape.
title: Amazon ‘misunderstood’ in AI race, says AWS chief; claims platform now strongest

author: TNN
description: A 30-year-old nurse was allegedly gang-raped by three men in a hotel room in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar after she mistakenly knocked on their door. The accused, including two recovery agents and an MBA student, were arrested and remanded in police custody. The victim had gone to meet a friend for financial assistance when the incident occurred.
title: Maharashtra horror: Nurse gang-raped after knocking on wrong hotel room; 3 arrested

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: A near-collision occurred in space when a new Chinese satellite came within 200 meters of a SpaceX Starlink satellite. SpaceX blamed the Chinese launch provider, CAS Space, for not sharing location data and coordinating satellite deployments. CAS Space stated its responsibility ends after deployment but is investigating the incident and emphasizes international cooperation for space safety.
title: Starlink reports 200m near-collision: calls out no coordination; Chinese launch provider replies

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Bill Goldberg, a wrestling icon, boasts a net worth of $16 million in 2025, primarily from his WWE career and merchandise. His wife, Wanda Ferraton, an actress turned businesswoman, contributes $1 million to their combined $17 million fortune. The couple, married since 2005, now balances family life with their ongoing professional endeavors.
title: Bill Goldberg & Wanda Ferraton Net Worth 2025: WWE earnings and investments

author: TNN
description: In a dramatic turn of events at Delhi airport, an Air India Express pilot found himself grounded after supposedly attacking a passenger amidst a scuffle over a security queue. The passenger described the ordeal, sharing how he emerged with a bloodied face before the pilot’s scheduled flight to Bengaluru.
title: 'Cutting the queue': AI Express grounds pilot over assault on passenger; probe on

author: SHAFAQUE ALAM AND AYANTIKA PAL
description: Commuters faced significant disruption as Delhi enforced a ban on non-BS 6 vehicles from other states, leading to confusion and fines at border checkpoints. Many were turned back or forced to take lengthy detours, highlighting a lack of coordination and public awareness regarding the new pollution control measures.
title: Delhi-NCR, interrupted: Day 2 of border troubles & tempers

title: Goa: 18 months after NGT order, Curlies sealed for violations

author: VIMAL BHATIA
description: Six individuals, including a German couple, were detained in Sriganganagar for alleged illegal religious conversions. The group was found in a rented house in Srikaranpur, a town near the India-Pakistan border. Authorities are investigating the German nationals' presence in a restricted border zone without authorization.
title: German couple detained for 'illegal religious conversions' near Indo-Pak border; 4 others held

title: Op Hawkeye: US launches airstrikes on ISIS targets in Syria; move after death of 2 American soldiers

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Following the deaths of two American soldiers and a US civilian interpreter in Syria, President Trump announced Operation Hawkeye Strike, a severe retaliation against ISIS targets. The US is striking ISIS strongholds in Deir ez-Zor, Raqqa, and near Palmyra, aiming at weapons depots and command centers. Trump issued a stern warning to any group threatening the USA.
title: 'Will be hit harder if ... ': Trump's warning as US strikes ISIS targets in Syria
